dcterms:description: The Mackey-Glass time series is a chaotic time series generated by a non-linear time-delay differential equation. It is commonly used for benchmarking forecasting tasks due to its deterministic yet chaotic nature.
dcterms:title: Mackey-Glass Time Series

dcterms:creator: K. Bache
M. Lichman
dcterms:description: The Individual Household Electric Power Consumption dataset contains measurements of power consumption for a single residential customer, gathered between December 2006 and November 2010, with a one-minute resolution. The dataset includes aggregate active power load for the whole house and sub-metering for three sections of the house.
dcterms:title: Individual Household Electric Power Consumption
